.TH NIC-XRAY 8 "2026-02-27" "1.4" "System Administration Commands"
.SH NAME
nic-xray \- network interface diagnostic tool
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B nic-xray
[\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B nic-xray
lists all physical network interfaces on the system, displaying detailed
information in a color-coded table. Information shown includes PCI slot,
firmware version, MAC address, MTU, link status, negotiated speed/duplex,
bond/LAG membership, and LLDP peer information.
.PP
The tool was originally created for deploying OpenStack nodes but works on
any Linux system. It must be run as root.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-\-lacp
Show LACP Aggregator ID and Partner MAC per interface.
.TP
.B \-\-vlan
Show VLAN tagging information obtained via LLDP.
.TP
.B \-\-bmac
Show bridge MAC address.
.TP
.BI \-s\fR[\fISEP\fR]\fB,\ \-\-separator\fR[=\fISEP\fR]
Show column separators in table output (default: \fBâ”‚\fR). Applies to CSV
output as well. Optionally specify a custom separator character \fISEP\fR.
.TP
.B \-\-group\-bond
Sort output rows by bond group, then by interface name within each group.
.TP
.BI \-\-output \ TYPE
Select output format. Supported types:
.RS
.TP
.B table
Human-readable tabular output (default).
.TP
.B csv
Comma-separated values suitable for spreadsheet import.
.TP
.B json
JSON output suitable for scripting and automation.
.RE
.TP
.BR \-v ,\  \-\-version
Print the version number and exit.
.TP
.BR \-h ,\  \-\-help
Print a usage summary and exit.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success.
.TP
.B 1
A required command is missing, or the script was invoked without root privileges,
or an invalid option was specified.
.SH REQUIREMENTS
.B nic-xray
must be run as root. The following commands must be available:
.BR ethtool (8),
.BR lldpctl (8)
(provided by
.IR lldpd ),
.BR ip (8),
.BR readlink (1),
.BR awk (1),
.BR grep (1),
.BR cat (1).
.SH EXAMPLES
Show all interfaces with default table output:
.PP
.RS
.nf
sudo nic-xray
.fi
.RE
.PP
Show LACP and VLAN information:
.PP
.RS
.nf
sudo nic-xray --lacp --vlan
.fi
.RE
.PP
Export interface data as JSON:
.PP
.RS
.nf
sudo nic-xray --output json
.fi
.RE
.PP
Group output by bond membership:
.PP
.RS
.nf
sudo nic-xray --group-bond
.fi
.RE
